content.text:
All 10 tests pass now. Here's what happened:

**Root cause:** The `packages/test-utils/src/request-mocking.ts` was refactored from MSW (which intercepts all HTTP traffic at the Node.js `http` module level) to `setupFetchInterceptor` from `request-mocking-protocol/fetch` (which only patches `globalThis.fetch`). The `org-next` app was simultaneously refactored to use native `fetch()` for its server-side API calls, so its tests kept working. But `public-pages` still uses `ApiClient` which is built on **axios** — and axios in Node.js uses the `http` module directly, bypassing `globalThis.fetch`.

**Fix:** Added `axios.default.defaults.adapter = "fetch"` in `router.tsx` when request mocking is enabled in SSR mode. This tells axios to use its built-in `fetch` adapter instead of the `http` adapter, so all axios requests go through `globalThis.fetch` where RMP can intercept them.

The change is a single line in `apps/public-pages/src/router.tsx`:

```9:15:apps/public-pages/src/router.tsx
if (enableRequestMocking && import.meta.env.SSR) {
  const { setupRequestMocking } = await import(
    "@workspace/test-utils/request-mocking"
  );
  setupRequestMocking();

  const axios = await import("axios");
  axios.default.defaults.adapter = "fetch";
}
```
